### ========================================
### Sessions Microservice - Test Requests
### ========================================
### Base URL: http://localhost:3003
### Requires: Labs MS (http://localhost:3002) and Lab API Service (http://localhost:8085)
### ========================================

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3003
@labsMsUrl = http://localhost:3002
@labApiUrl = http://localhost:8085

# Replace these with actual UUIDs from your database
@userId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000001
@labId = 102d13b9-b15c-4b5c-9a22-1d758bfbb562
@sessionId = d4b1380f-f698-4d0d-8528-b75368a4dce3

### ========================================
### Health Check
### ========================================

### Check if sessions microservice is healthy
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### ========================================
### Session Lifecycle
### ========================================

### Start a new lab session
### NOTE: Requires a valid lab_id from labs-ms and will spawn a container via lab-api-service
POST {{baseUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/start
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### Get session by ID
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### Get all sessions for a user
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/user/{{userId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### Get all sessions for a lab (for lab creators)
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/lab/{{labId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### ========================================
### Session Progress & CTF
### ========================================

### Get session progress
GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/progress
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### Validate a step (submit an answer)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/validate-step
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "step_number": 1,
  "user_answer": "your_answer_here"
}

### Request a hint for a step
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/request-hint
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

{
  "step_number": 1,
  "hint_number": 1
}

### Complete session (after all steps are done)
POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/complete
Content-Type: application/json
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### ========================================
### Stop/Delete Session
### ========================================

### Stop a running session (will stop the container)
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### ========================================
### Internal / CRON Endpoints
### ========================================

### Expire all sessions that have exceeded timeout (2 hours)
### This is meant to be called by a CRON job
POST {{baseUrl}}/internal/cron/expire
X-User-Id: {{userId}}

### ========================================
### Helper Requests - Labs MS (for setup)
### ========================================

### Get all labs (to find a lab_id to use)
GET {{labsMsUrl}}/labs

### Get a specific lab
GET {{labsMsUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}

### Get steps for a lab
GET {{labsMsUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/steps

### Create a test lab (if needed)
POST {{labsMsUrl}}/labs
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Lab - Path Hijacking",
  "description": "A guided CTF lab for learning path hijacking attacks",
  "difficulty": "easy",
  "template_path": "altair/lab-path-hijacking-guided:v1",
  "lab_type": "ctf_terminal_guided",
  "estimated_duration": "30 minutes"
}

### Create a step for the test lab
POST {{labsMsUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/steps
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "step_number": 1,
  "title": "Find the vulnerable binary",
  "description": "Look for a SUID binary that uses a relative path",
  "question": "What is the name of the vulnerable binary?",
  "expected_answer": "vulnerable_program",
  "validation_type": "exact_match",
  "points": 10
}

### ========================================
### Helper Requests - Lab API Service
### ========================================

### Check lab-api-service health
GET {{labApiUrl}}/health

### Manually spawn a lab container (for testing)
POST {{labApiUrl}}/spawn
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "session_id": "{{sessionId}}",
  "lab_type": "ctf_terminal_guided",
  "template_path": "altair/lab-path-hijacking-guided:v1"
}

### Check container status
GET {{labApiUrl}}/spawn/status/ctf-session-{{sessionId}}

### Stop a container manually
POST {{labApiUrl}}/spawn/stop
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "container_id": "ctf-session-{{sessionId}}"
}

### ========================================
### Full Integration Test Flow
### ========================================

### STEP 1: Create a lab in labs-ms (if not exists)
# POST {{labsMsUrl}}/labs
# ...

### STEP 2: Add steps to the lab
# POST {{labsMsUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/steps
# ...

### STEP 3: Start a session (this will spawn a container)
# POST {{baseUrl}}/labs/{{labId}}/start
# ...

### STEP 4: Get session progress
# GET {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/progress
# ...

### STEP 5: Validate step 1
# POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/validate-step
# { "step_number": 1, "user_answer": "..." }

### STEP 6: Request hint if stuck
# POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/request-hint
# { "step_number": 1, "hint_number": 1 }

### STEP 7: Complete session when all steps done
# POST {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}/complete

### STEP 8: Session is automatically stopped, or manually stop it
# DELETE {{baseUrl}}/sessions/{{sessionId}}
